Pfizer Asks F.D.A. to Authorize Vaccine for Children 5 to 11

  • The agency has promised to move quickly on the request and has tentatively scheduled a meeting at the end of the month to consider it.
  • Pfizer has proposed giving children one-third of the adult dosage. F.D.A. authorization could help protect more than 28 million children in the U.S.

What’s in Our Queue? Portraits and More

What’s in Our Queue? Portraits and More

I’m a deputy editor and art director on the Culture desk at The Times.

I’ve been thinking about faces lately.

Here are five things I’ve been watching and reading which demonstrate that →

What’s in Our Queue? Portraits and More

TV: ‘Portrait Artist of the Year’

In this series for Sky Arts, competing artists have four hours to paint a celebrity sitter. The drama is charmingly measured: a nose appears at the last minute, or a false stroke suddenly muddles the composition.

What’s in Our Queue? Portraits and More

Art Book: ‘Alice Neel, Uptown’

Neel, the great Harlem portraitist, painted neighbors and friends — some well-known, others more anonymous. You can view her work in “Alice Neel, Uptown,” a book from the essayist and critic Hilton Als.

What’s in Our Queue? Portraits and More

Book: ‘Stranger Faces’

In this pocket-size book of short essays, the critic and novelist Namwali Serpell considers the problem of faces, particularly those that may seem strange to us. Her sharp and often funny writing ranges widely across subjects and ideas.

What’s in Our Queue? Portraits and More

Documentary: ‘The Upsetter’

I saw the reggae legend Lee (Scratch) Perry perform when he was 77. He could still electrify a room. When he died in August, I watched this doc, narrated by Benicio Del Toro, which tells Perry’s wild story.

What’s in Our Queue? Portraits and More

TV: ‘Formula 1: Drive to Survive’

I didn’t expect this documentary series about Formula 1 racing to be for me. But the elite drivers here — each vying for their own legacy — are ready-made for dramatic television. Heroes and villains emerge.
